body_html:
@achowdhery i trained the same model with these checkpoints :

ssd_mobilenet_v1_coco_2017_11_17

ssdlite_mobilenet_v2_coco_2018_05_09

I downloaded both of them from here ssd_mobilenet_v1_coco and ssdlite_mobilenet_v2_coco

but the ssd_mobilenet_v1 is now updated, when you download it you will get this file : ssd_mobilenet_v1_coco_2018_01_28 but i think you can use it because it won't affect the problem I mentioned since it occurs with the ssdlite model.

Final question :
Does this model works better with TFLite ? since I'm testing with TF mobile.

body:
@achowdhery i trained the same model with these checkpoints : 

`ssd_mobilenet_v1_coco_2017_11_17`

`ssdlite_mobilenet_v2_coco_2018_05_09`

I downloaded both of them from [here](https://github.com/tensorflow/models/blob/master/research/object_detection/g3doc/detection_model_zoo.md) `ssd_mobilenet_v1_coco `and `ssdlite_mobilenet_v2_coco`

but the `ssd_mobilenet_v1` is now updated, when you download it you will get this file : `ssd_mobilenet_v1_coco_2018_01_28` but i think you can use it because it won't affect the problem I mentioned since it occurs with the `ssdlite` model.

 Final question : 
Does this model works better with `TFLite` ? since I'm testing with `TF mobile`.
